Sentencas: In this paper, a numerical model of gas flow, heat transfer, mass transfer and electrochemical reaction multi-physics field coupling of a planar SOFC is established and solved.
Titulo: Multiphysics Coupling Simulation and Parameter Study of Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: According to the calculation results, the distribution of velocity, temperature and concentration inside the SOFC cell is analyzed.
Titulo: Multiphysics Coupling Simulation and Parameter Study of Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The influence of cathode inlet flow rate, porosity, rib width and other parameters on the performance of SOFC is also discussed.
Titulo: Multiphysics Coupling Simulation and Parameter Study of Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The results show that within a certain range, increasing the cathode inlet flow rate can significantly increase the average current density of the cell.
Titulo: Multiphysics Coupling Simulation and Parameter Study of Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Increasing the porosity of the electrode can improve the gas diffusion of the porous electrode, thereby increasing the rate of the electrochemical reaction.
Titulo: Multiphysics Coupling Simulation and Parameter Study of Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Increasing the width of the ribs will result in a significant decrease in cell performance.
Titulo: Multiphysics Coupling Simulation and Parameter Study of Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Therefore, the rib width should be reduced as much as possible within the allowable range to optimize the working performance of the cell.
Titulo: Multiphysics Coupling Simulation and Parameter Study of Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
